234
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:12,120
So find this threshold, find this predictor that 
tends to plateau that correlates strongly with  

235
00:20:12,120 --> 00:20:16,480
retention but with also the transaction 
happening, and that's the metric that you  

236
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:21,160
can predict. That's a metric that's so much more 
actionable for teams to work against. If you're  

237
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:26,240
a supply team now you can think of, "Okay, 
I'm adding 100 supplies into the platform.  

238
00:20:26,240 --> 00:20:31,400
I want to know if it's actually reducing ETAs 
