284
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:25,000
marketplace is a good model for the idea? Because 
I think a lot of people come into and be like,  

285
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:28,760
"I want to build a marketplace. Oh, I'm going to 
connect these two sides. It's going to be great,"  

286
00:24:28,760 --> 00:24:32,360
and there's no marketplace in this 
business, in this vertical. What are  

287
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:40,000
signs that marketplace dynamic and a business 
model is right for an idea versus no, it's not?

288
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:44,080
No one ever say like, "Oh, I'm going to build 
Airbnb for X," it's not something that people  

289
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:54,360
say. I think the signs that come to mind are 
one, higher fragmentation. I think you want  

290
00:24:54,360 --> 00:24:59,080
this long tail of buyers and sellers without a 
handful of big players controlling the market,  

291
00:24:59,080 --> 00:25:04,760
because this is where you can provide value by 
doing this job of aggregation. I think you also  

292
00:25:04,760 --> 00:25:10,400
want a relatively uniform set of needs. That 
means that it can be, like your supply can  

293
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:15,920
be commoditized to some extent. This is what's 
so tricky, by the way, about services, service  

