297
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:36,960
cancel it because something better comes up.
And so, this makes for a very fuzzy definition  

298
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:43,520
of supply, and you have very different set 
of needs. One electrician wants something,  

299
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:48,280
the other one has a very different perception of 
the same unit of demand, and that makes it very,  

300
00:25:48,280 --> 00:25:52,440
very difficult. So, it's feasible, but I 
would say that is not a compelling attribute  

301
00:25:52,440 --> 00:25:58,360
for building a marketplace. So, a relatively 
uniform set of needs. And the last one I'd  

302
00:25:58,360 --> 00:26:08,720
mention is a high enough bearer in the matchmaking 
or the creation. I think how hard it is for people  

303
00:26:08,720 --> 00:26:13,960
to find each other today, and how much effort 
do they have to put in to vet each other,  

304
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:18,280
I think is another great sign. The higher 
it is, the bigger the opportunity because  

305
00:26:18,280 --> 00:26:24,720
it means you come in, implement the right 
